<h2>
    Required Licenses and Regulations
</h2>
<h3>
    Oregon Fishing License Information
</h3>
<p>
    All anglers over age 12 need a valid <strong>Oregon fishing license</strong>, which can be obtained online through the ODFW website.
</p>
<h3>
    Bag Limits and Legal Methods
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Daily Limit:</strong> 2 trout per day in most areas (check local signage)
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Legal Methods:</strong> Both bait and artificial flies/lures are allowed in most waters, but some rivers are restricted to artificial flies only during certain seasons.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    Conservation Guidelines
</h3>
<p>
    Catch-and-release is highly encouraged, especially for <strong>wild cutthroat trout</strong>, identifiable by their intact adipose fin. Handle fish gently, and release them quickly to support healthy populations.
</p>
<h2>
